The Colt Diamondback is a revolver manufactured by Colt's Manufacturing Company of Hartford, Connecticut, in calibers of .22 LR, .22 WMR and .38 Special. Colt introduced the double-action Diamondback as a deluxe model. It had a wide serrated target hammer, ventilated rib, fully adjustable target quality sights, and full-length barrel underlug. It is a 6-shot revolver with a swing out cylinder and was available in blue or nickel finishes. Visually, the Diamondback resembles a scaled down version of the Python. Because of the light recoil of .22 caliber ammunition, the .22 version of the Diamondback can be used as a training gun for novice shooters. title: For Sale/Trade:  Upgrade your new AR to a Black Rain Ordnance- at retail pricing
postcontent:
I bought an awesome Black Rain Ordnance .223 AR about a month ago that has a 24" brl. It's unfired, all black, has 1 pmag, and the factory soft case. As much as I like AR's, I hate having almost $2300 bucks in a rifle I can't go deer hunting with. What I'm really looking for is a cheaper AR like a Bushmaster, Core 15, Windham etc in .556 to go plinking with. I know there's a bunch of people that have settled for the less expensive models because that's all they can get their hands on at the retails stores lately.

So here's the deal, if you've got a NIB AR, or even a slightly used one (like 1 mag run through it to sight it in) in perfect condition that you have the receipt on, show me the receipt, pay me the difference between $2253 ($2100 + tax is what I paid at a Wichita gun store), we swap guns and away you go with a Black Rain. I don't need your optics, additional mags, ammo, sling, or other acc. We only swap what came with the rifle new. If you've got the box, sweet, but not a deal breaker. I'll only swap AR to AR, no AK's, or other tactical models. And NO, I don't want to trade for tools or an 89 Chevy Pickup.

If you're not familiar with Black Rain AR's, check out their website. These are top end high quality rifles.

I'd like to keep my total dollars in an AR below $1500. Current retail pricing from local Wichita gun shops only is what I'll consider. If you got hosed on Gunbroker and paid $1500 for an $800 rifle-sorry can't help you. I'm not dead set on any particular model to trade for so let me know what you've got.

If this interests you, shoot me a picture/e-mail about what you have and I'll send you some pictures of my Black Rain. I'm going to be in and out of data range the next couple of days so I might be a little slow responding to e-mail-but I will respond.

Face to face transaction in Wichita only.

Thanks!
